Legit Italian here. I'm always skeptical when American friends ask me to try an Italian place. I was pleasantly surprised. Food was delicious. It has an Italian tradition twist with a touch of modern in there. Service was great and the ambiance was nice as well.
Ambiance was perfect in the wine selection is to die for also it's not commercialized Italian
Tagliata to go is very good. The food is O’mazing and the general Manager Stephen and his team go above and beyond.

I was there for lunch. The only thing that kept them from a five star was the long wait. There was no one there at the host station. And no one, and no one. It appeared someone was doing a wine tasting in the bar. But none of them seemed concerned that I and another woman were waiting at the host station. Once I was seen, the whole occasion turned around. The server was very courteous. I had a lunch portion and a small salad. The bread crisp on top of the Ceasar salad was great. It gave a little extra crunch to the salad. The pasta was delicious and the service once seated was on spot!

Had a very  nice time celebrating my wifes birthday. They opened the outdoor patio so we were able to eat outdoors, which is our preferred level of comfort right now. The service was great, the waitress was very knowledgable and happy to answer any, and all questions we had. All of the food we had was very good. I highly recommend the meatballs and calamari as appetizers, and the tortellini as a main dish. The tuna was also cooked to perfection and was delicious.  Pictured are: Tortellini - prosciutto filled pasta, sicilian pistachi cream sauce Braised duck Ragu - tagliatelle, parmigiano, gremolata Lobster ravioli - mascarpone, lemon, lobster cream sauce Calamari - fregola sarda, olives, capers, line nuts, golden raisins, calabrian chili Polpette meatballs - classic tagliata meatballs, tomato sauce, whipped ricotta, basil
Warm atmosphere, friendly staff and delicious food I tried Lobster Ravioli and I like it . They offer indoor and outdoor tables.

Delicious food, excellent service and live piano tunes! We had a great time and would come back again.
I am not joking when I say that I often dream about the squid ink campanelle from Tagliata. It is so delicious and so worth the visit! If I could I would eat it everyday!
Ambiance fabulous

Tasty food and great service. Special thanks to Morgan for excellent drinks!!

I found my next favourite italian restaurant in Baltimore. My past favourite is temporarily closed but I think Tagliata will now be my favourite! Clean restaurant, excellent food and good service. The server did not hover and clear the dishes away while one of us was still eating. I hate when they do that. It feels as though they are rushing. I highly recommend.  Visited again yesterday and was amazing. Pricy restaurant but worth it. Yesterday, we had lunch to celebrate me getting my vaccine. It was totally worth it!
Got there late, bartender needs more welcoming skills. Decent service just had to keep asking for it.

Had a great table outside and weather was good. Beautiful patio and lights . Enjoyed the appetizer bread . The chilled corn soup was best and the rigatoni pasta was amazing . Great dessert as well . Fantastic. Dinner with business colleagues. I highly recommended this restaurant.

Very good restaurant. The vibe is perfect for a romantic date or a calm family outing. The food was so good, I had squid ink campanelle and my wife had lobster ravioli. They were so good, even our 1 yr old daughter loved it. I would definitely recommend it to anyone for a date night or celebration.
Great food, ambiance and excellent service!
Great service. I had the meatballs, oysters, and espresso martini and all were 10/10
Great pasta. The lobster ravioli was my favorite

The squid ink pasta was delicious. The fried chicken was great as well, service was wonderful  and the Panna Cotta dessert was exquisite. I wouldn't dmsuggest the calamari unless you know what you are getting yourself into. But over  loved the food would go there again for sure

I loved everything about it! Even the smallest details of the bread and butter were delicious. I had the tortellini and loved it. My date had the bolognese and couldn't get enough! Before the main courses we enjoyed the bruschetta (which was so unique and amazing) and meatballs. The ricotta just takes it to new levels. I loved this place and am definitely coming back!
Loved the ambiance and the wine was awesome..

Tag is a special restaurant.  Julian, the executive chef is almost always working. He inspects every plate before it goes out.  The food is creative, beautiful,  and very flavorful. The pasta is delicate and delicious. The service is great, the entire staff is attentive. Tag is my go to place for a great night out.

The service was awful and felt like they were trying to rush you out. I completely understand they are operating under the mayor's guidelines during COVID, but being asked multiple times by multiple different people if we are ready to get a box for our food when we are in the midst of taking a bite is not a fine dining experience. Nowhere in the restaurant or on any booking sites for reservations do they mention this time limit, yet they mention the dress code multiple times inside the restaurant and on sites like OpenTable, their own website, etc. They say they are business casual yet the waiters and hostess' are in light wash jeans. I grew up with homemade Italian food for dinner constantly and this food was painfully average. The meatballs were over cooked, not tender at all, and cold. The bruschetta, bread and butter were over salted. I will never go back. Ambiance was incredible but they sat people so close to you. Why follow some COVID guidelines but not all? Also way overpriced for the average food.
One of my preferred locations for delicious Italian food. Loved this place from the first taste. Feeling here is similar to a cafe in San Jose I liked.
Excellent! Highly Recommend!

The ambiance is great for an intimate dinner. There was a live pianist accompanied by singer the night we dined. All four of us thoroughly enjoyed our meals. I realize these are difficult times for the service industry but the waits for service on food and drink was beyond expectations.

G and I decided to finally try Tagliata as we were staying nearby at the Hyatt Place. I had a certain level of skepticism as we approached the complex that was piping Italian American standards to the street...  We sat and ordered two cocktails. I had the Belzoni and was pleasantly impressed with the gratifying taste of a wonderful blend of rye with two Amaros of which I as unfamiliar, and just a touch of smoothing honey.  I will be picking up a bottle of at least one of the amaros for my own bar. G had a wonderful concoction of tequila, mezcal and hints of chili, and beamed at the first taste.  The fluffy bread was served with whipped butter and bits of perfect Parmesan cheese. Seems like it should be basic, yet I can’t recall receiving the trio elsewhere.  We split a Cesar salad and G commented on the amazing dressing, then promptly ordered a glass of Prosecco in anticipation of the forthcoming house-made pasta.  Her lobster Fra. Diavolo was divine. An appropriately sized half-order with chunks of meat and spicy sauce that paired nicely with the bubbles.  I enjoyed a scrumptious marrying of blue crab and sea urchin cream sauce in the squid ink campanelle. I almost regretted not expanding to the full order (Covid weight).  We couldn’t resist trying the trio of house-made gelatos with tea and coffee, and we weren’t disappointed.  I hadn’t realized they are an Italian chophouse, with an adventurous chef that is as proud of his cuts as he is with the pasta.  We can’t wait for dinner!
Great food, great service. The atmosphere was nice as well. Definitely recommend

My friend and I had an amazing time it was some of the best Italian food I have ever had and the environment is gorgeous makes for amazing pictures and a good environment for a date. And the staff truly makes all the Atlas restaurants my go to spot when I am home on leave from the Marines. Its an escape from reality into an amazing experience.
Excellent food and service!
Exceptional!
The ambience of the outdoor dining was super cute! The food was DELICIOUS!! Can't wait to return😊🍷
Love it here! Delicious food and drinks. Cozy atmosphere.
Loved the place food was great had a good time!
Awesome and tasty food, I like the vibes this spot has, and the cashiers were nice. I will definitely visit here when I’m around.

Five stars! I’ve been here twice, I believe, and each time I have not been disappointed. I really love this restaurant and the food is so so delicious. The ambiance of the restaurant is fantastic. I love the outside decoration that they have of what seems like Christmas lights. This restaurant is truly one of the best places in Baltimore. The staff goes above and beyond. Five stars.
Crazy fantastic place to eat. I only wish I had the money to go more often. One of my absolute favorites in Baltimore.
Food is great ambiance is relaxed and easy. Price is expected for the food and worth it. You wont go away feeling cheated and will be full to remind you.
the atmosphere, the food, the lighting, and the folks it was a nice element... enjoyed my experience
The bolognese was incredible. Service and atmosphere are perfect

Stopped in for a meal while visiting and was really blown away. The bread and butter with chunks of parmesan was incredible and the bolognese was to die for.
Food and staff were great.  Went for my fiancée birthday and they brought us free champagne.
The cutest outdoor space and the absolute best bolognese I’ve ever had. Good wine and Cesar salad. Great staff

I would have given 5 stars because I have eaten here once and it was amazing. I tried to order food tonight to go and waiting on hold for 5 minutes to even try to place an order. I'm not in the mood to sit on hold for a $50 meal.
Pretentious and rude staff. One manager rudely told me to take off my hat. I wear it because it keeps me from getting anxiety about my balding hair. Never again.

The atmosphere and service are top notch and the live music is icing on the cake for a lovely, romantic date night. The songstress playing the piano was amazing! And I can’t forget to mention the food! The chefs definitely know what they are doing, you can’t go wrong with any selection on the menu. My husband and I will definitely be coming back for this memorable dining experience!

Very much overpriced for the food  and atmosphere. Food is good but a small dish of pasta should not cost $30 a plate. A simple and small  Cesar salad should not be  $14. Very disappointed. Had 9 people to celebrate my birthday and it cost us enough to have 20 people in any other very good restaurant

I was here a wk ago, Im back because the food, atmosphere, service & live piano were great. Tomight I came by myself & was quite comfortable sitting on a velour coach. The first night we had pasta, tonight I went for the calamari, caeser salad & a peach bellini. Even though Ive been eating fewer carbs, I just had to eat their bread with delicious butter. I also had a lovely cappucino tonight. The first night we shared an absolutely delicious chocolate dessert. I would definitely recommend Tagliata & make sure you make reservations as the secret is out! This place is great solo, for a date, gals night out or with your family.

This is one of my favorite spots ever for Italian food! I love the quality of food, service, and atmosphere that you get while dining here. I’ve had quite a few dishes and feel like you can’t go wrong with any of them. The squid ink campanelle is a really unique dish that you can’t get anywhere else, so this place is worth the trip for that alone! The Tuscan fried chicken is my go-to appetizer and the ricotta bomboloni for dessert are outstanding. I can’t wait to return!
Great atmosphere, food was also great.

italian food and the atmosphere here is excellent. Service is always awesome even when they have a full house. Had a sister come into town and asked me to take her here again. The bill was fair for the quality of food. This place has many great reviews for a reason.

The food was beautiful. Well balanced and good composition of flavors. They do have a business casual policy in place for indoor dining, but that really just elevated the dining experience. Service was great. Highly recommend!

I was really excited to come here to celebrate a friend’s birthday, however, I ended up being extremely disappointed. The ambience was great, however the service wasn’t. Our server wasn’t bad, just not attentive enough, especially when trying to flag him down because of my over-priced, undercooked dish. By the time I got a new dish, the rest of my party finished their meals and were ready for the check. It’s not like the place was extremely busy either. I don’t like to leave bad reviews, however it’s best to warn anyone reading this to keep your expectations low. Tagliata wants to be this 4-5 star restaurant, but you can’t fake your way to that, no matter how well you dress yourself up in photos. If you like subpar restaurants with pretty lighting, this place is for you.

My favorite place for tasty Italian food. Normally I would have posted a pic but food looked so good I couldn't stop. The staff was very helpful and welcoming. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I liked.

The charcuterie board was a hit at my table as well.  For a nice romantic date night spot, or a cool group dinner checkout Tagliata for sure.

The outdoor garden is a lovely spot for a meal, and the indoors looked luxurious as well (love the open kitchen). I had a couple antipasti and the flavors were bright and seasonal and made for a perfect light lunch. I hope to come back and try their pasta soon!

had lunch for two people, ordered an appetizer + 2 dishes + one dessert. The waiter suggested that we order a "full" portion for each dish instead of "half" portion. We ended up ordering one full portion and one half portion. When the food arrived, we realized "half" portion is actually plenty for one person. We wasted so much money and had to take the food home. If you go and order food there, you'll see what I mean. DO NOT listen to the waiter if he or she suggests one person should order one "full" portion each.

Have been to tagliata several times during the pandemic because me and my wife had the time. Each time we visited the food was excellent the atmosphere was excellent we were sitting outside in the courtyard. This time we set inside and the food was excellent as usual. But we feel extremely cheated because the dacor was horrible. We felt like we were at Denny's or the Double T Diner. We've eaten at several Atlas Group restaurants. And the day quora tagliata is grossly overrated and it needs to be taken care of immediately. The wicker chairs inside unacceptable the mirror that's it behind my wife was filthy the drapes that separated the rooms were filthy. To Alex Smith I'm quite sure you demand better and for our hard-earned money we expect better. It's needs to be taken care of because the dacor does not match or even come close to living up to the service and the food I can honestly say when we were sitting there eating and looking at the dacor and seeing the curtains we lost our appetite. We expect better and mr. Smith I'm quite sure you demand better for your restaurants we've been to the loch bar several times. We frequently disco Pizza and we've been to Ouzo Bay to which the decor and ambiance and service was excellent we did not agree with the food. But that's okay. We expect more from tagliata.

Excellent food and excellent service spectacular atmosphere in the outdoor corredor. Each and every song was a good and classy jazz Classic. We'll definitely be back.
My food was not as hot
Such a great experience and great food. Will definitely return.

I should start by mentioning that I usually avoid food that is considered 'fancy' fearful that I am not going to care for it. We started with delicious complimentary bread, butter and cheese. There were 10 of us and we shared a charcuterie board. Delicious prosciutto. Some of my other family members were more adventurous and enjoyed it all. We split a couple orders of meatballs, some 'chicken bites' and some fish. The meatballs are made with beef, pork and veal. I don't know what the chicken appetizer is called but it was the tastiest chicken I have ever had. I also don't know what the fish is called.
Delicious!!

Great food!

I have been working in Baltimore for 32 years and have eaten numerous great meals, however, this is one of the few places you must avoid based on my experience.  $65 for a NY Strip a la carte, which I ordered Very Rare and it was DONE to DEATH, I mean killed.  I was with a large  group from work, one of my co-workers recommended that we should go here with an out of town client, so I did not want to make a scene and it back.  This was hands down the worst meal I have ever had in a Baltimore restaurant in 32 years.  Possibly, this was an exception, but I will never go back here again. Stopped by mid-week for dinner and really enjoyed it. I tried the risotto and my father tried the lasagna (he sticks to the classics). Both were excellent as was the meatball appetizer. Service was friendly and attentive. Give Tagliata a try if you find yourself in the area!
When I'm back in Baltimore, I will definitely go back!

Great first experience. There menu is seasonal and flavorful. The squid ink pasta was delicious! Their pasta is hand made, thus eating a half bowl appeared to be a very satisfying and light entree. In regards to customer service, our waitress was amazing.She was attentive, offered accurate descriptions of the food, and most importantly created a relaxed atmosphere. We were a party of 4 plus our 5 month old. Our baby was well behaved (no outburst, nor destructive behavior), which I noticed some staff were surprised. However,  not one staff member exhibit any words and physical expressions that caused our party to feel uncomfortable.

Had a celebratory dinner for my daughter’s graduation.  The food was phenomenal. The service was on point. The food  recommendations were superb. We even got a visit to our table by the chef. Great experience. Highly recommend.

Fantastic atmosphere and fantastic food. The servers and wait staff were amazing and worked so hard to make this a great meal. The dishes were creative and flavorful. Would love to eat here again.
Excellent service and food. Great lunch sized portions. Lovely atmosphere and great drinks. Love to come here for lunch, dinner, and drinks!
Food, drink, service, atmosphere were all amazing!

This restaurant has a great location in Harbor East with a cozy and cute dining area. The staff was friendly and great at bringing out courses on time and recommending drinks. You must try a cappuccino and some gelato, it was my favorite part of the meal! My only con for this place is that the food is underwhelming, I tried recommend dishes, and while the food was good, nothing was great. Would return for drinks, service, appetizers, and desert, but probably not for main dishes.

I had a great birthday dinner here yesterday. We were able to call in a reservation an hour before hand. We got there a little bit early and had a few drinks at the bar and listened to the live piano player. The vibes are very cool and laid-back. We had a charcuterie board which was fantastic, I highly recommend the prosciutto. For dinner I had the squid ink pasta dish which was absolutely fantastic and generous on the crab meat. My boyfriend have the Bolognese which he said was a little bit dry but fixed up well with the addition of some olive oil. We had gelato and cake for dessert. The service was amazing and I had a fantastic time. I would totally go here again and have been recommending the squid ink pasta dish to literally everybody
great food, drinks, service and parking was a breeze
Loved it multiple times
I don’t have words for how amazing the food is!!

Very over priced for what you get. We were not satisfied with the food. It wasn't as good as it should have been for what we were paying. We had dined at fleet street kitchen many times before and the food was way better.
Delicious food and outstanding service.  Our server Emily knew the menu inside and out and was able to make fantastic recommendations.  Wonderful experience!

Tagliata is an excellent dining experience. Everything ordered was amazing. The chicken appetizer was arguably the best prepared chicken I've had. service was fast, friendly, and responsive. The menu is a moderate size with plenty of options  but not overwhelming. While the prices aren't barging prices they are a great value for quality of the dining experience. They're located near the harbor and other trendy shopping options. The decor is rustic eccentric and very visually captivating. I reccomend the bolognese and the lasagna. Trying to get a reservation is nearly impossible!!! I called on a Wednesday and was told because of it being a large party, I’d have to email. Ridiculous. I emailed the same person 4 times before receiving a response and then they were booked. GO FIGURE!!!  There needs to be a simpler solution. Making a reservation isn’t rocket science!!!👎🏼
Very average food with decent service. Not even close to LaScala, which is just on next block. And very expensive.
Food was delicious. We had Alex as our server and he was great! We will absolutely return again! I highly recommend the white chocolate gelato for dessert and the Peach Bellini for a drink :)

This restaurant is so beautiful and the employees  are lovely. It was my husbands 30th birthday and they wrote him a handwritten card, gave us two complimentary glasses of Prosecco 🥂 & a slice of cake, gelato and an adorable candle 🕯 to celebrate him. We’re both from Italian decent, and our family owns an Italian company here in the US, and we felt right at home here, even though it was our first time at this restaurant. Awesome place and I would give them more stars if I could. 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟

5stars are earned at Tagliata for one reason, and one reason only: communication. The rest is based on respect. Thankfully, there was plenty of both gravitating around and throughout the restaurant. Thanks for absorbing my input and I’m happy to have seen improvements before I ever departed!
They're not vegan friendly at all, and the service was mediocre both times I came here. You'd think for the area, they would be more accommodating.

Easily one of the top restaurants in Baltimore!  Food is excellent...we always get the calamari and the shaved Brussels sprouts.  Tonight they had burrata with acorn squash, a little on the sweet side but really tasty, they also had a foie gras and rabbit terrine with a garlicky mustard.  Perhaps the best entree is the lobster ravioli (we always order this) so we had that plus the rabbit confit and stufato.  The only miss was the rabbit tortellini which was nothing special and I would not recommend that dish.  The wine list is like a small novel!  Had to get help ordering wine...there were thousands to choose from.  We enjoyed the bottle of aglianico recommended.  Desserts are always superb, we had gelato/sorbeto, tiramisu and the dark chocolate fudge cake.  Can’t go wrong at Tagliata - great food, wine and attentive service.

My friend and I went for an early dinner on a Sunday night right before the dinner rush. I’m glad we did because this place gets busy and with good reason. Well-mannered staff, delicious food, sizable portions, and a warm and inviting ambiance. All around a really good time. 10/10 recommend and looking forward to returning for date night 😉
Love this place. The happy hour pasta deals are the best. Definitely not cheap but it certainly feels worth it
Good, but overpriced
Really amazing food and atmosphere. My friends rented the place for their rehearsal dinner and it was stunning!

Best Italian dishes in the city — on par with Little Italy’s loved restaurants. Love the decor and interior design, and love coming here year ‘round. Great staff. Menu is perfect for special occasions, or dinner with friends. Would recommend.
The service is phenomenal. The food is exquisite. I went to this place with a friend for her birthday and I just to go back a second time. Will definitely be back.
Good service and interesting food options but the quality is not worth the price.

I am disappointed with cost, customer services, taste of food and valet parking fee..They advertised free valet parking, but there is $12 mandatory parking  fee and of course plus valet's tip..(I don't think valets deserves any tip because they are rude).Food is extremely expensive for their small portions. Drinks are extremely expensive too. If do not wanna cry after seen yout check for  food and valet just go and eat somewhere else. I don't recommend  this restaurant to anyone.

Food and atmosphere was excellent! However, service was sub-par. When we entered, the hostesses were very attentive and welcoming, seating us within 2 minutes. We got seated at a table and patiently looked over the food and drink menu as it was our first time there. We ended up waiting 15 minutes for our server to greet us and then another 15 minutes for our drinks. When it came time to order our food, our server did recommend a good choice which I really enjoyed. The food came out in a reasonable time and was delicious. When we finished our meals, our server walked past us 5-6 times without acknowledging our finished plates. Eventually we had to ask another server for boxes and a dessert menu. We were there for two and a half hours, only ordering one drink and entree each and a dessert. I definitely would go back, but would hope for better service.
The service was good. I ordered chicken Parmesan with rigatoni pasta and I did not enjoy the pasta and parts of my chicken was burnt also the dish had to much sauce.

This place is great! We sat outside and the atmosphere was very chill. It sits between two buildings so it wasn't breezy and you almost don't even realize you are sitting outside. I ordered the squid ink pasta that had a ton of crab meat. My wife had the rissoto and she loved meal as well. Parking can be a pain so you definitely want to valet the car for $12. The menu is pricey, but that is to be expected most places downtown. If you like steaks and Italian food this place should be added to your list!

Amazing atmosphere and even better food. The mushroom bruschetta was beyond mouthwatering. Calamari was equally as good. The lasagna was made with lamb...I cleaned the dish. Not a speck left. Even Harry the bartender acknowledged it and said it was the cleanest plate hes ever received. Highly recommend and will return. Incredible first Tagliatta experience.
Great food!  While the service was a little slow....loved the food and the atmosphere!

The ambiance is beautiful. It feels like a NYC rooftop or a quaint Italian restaurant, but the food is very expensive and average. The full size pasta dishes are HUGE and $30. I ordered the gnocchi and hardly ate any because I didn't like it, so they offered to make me the penne with vodka sauce to go. I had it the next day and it was nothing special. It needed more sauce and lacked flavor. With quality Italian restaurants just up the street in Little Italy, we won't be back here for a very long time.
Amazing food. Extensive selection of Italian wines. Upbeat atmosphere.
Long waits for meals. Total PKG not a good value

The first time I came here for a friend’s birthday. The food was amazing, the service was even better. I felt like I never wondered where my server was and everything came out in a timely matter even though it was a busy Saturday night. The next time I came for my anniversary. The food was great, but the service wasn’t given with the same amount of effort, even though it was a slower Tuesday night. I’ve sat both outside and inside, both are great. Even though it’s a smaller restaurant, you don’t feel too cramped like you’re having dinner with whoever is sitting at the next table. I look forward to coming here again!
One of my favorite places in Baltimore. Service is excellent!!!.
First time there and it was GREATTTTT !!!  Happy Hour Menu is awesome. Good prices and good food.

I have dined here twice and each time was exquisite.  The atmosphere is relaxing and service is what you wish you encountered during every outing.  The simple must of an evening belongs to the Tuscan Fried Chicken, whether sitting at the bar or table side give it a try.

We've visited Tagliata twice, both times the service and ambiance would have sold us on returning, but the food is delicious. Please try the Tuscan fried chicken, the aged cowboy ribeye, the mushroom risotto, and for dessert- the coconut panna cotta.

Bar service was non existent. Servers looked at me at least 20 times and did not engage. I had to walk to the bar and walk back with my drinks. I don't understand how you can call this place a nice full service place. We say down at a table and ordered. The runner from the bar was the same woman who disregarded is at the bar. She dropped our drinks at the table and ran away Attitude could be sensed from accross the room. Table service was good but evening was shot at that point. We are locals and eat out 5+ times a week. We typically come here often but will reconsider this place after tonight. Food is good but don't expect service of any quality.
Best steak I have ever had.  Pasta is second to none.
Awesome menu beautiful decor, friendly staff!
Cool atmosphere with multiple spaces, great service, great food.
Delicious menu selection, incredible outdoor atmosphere, courteous & knowledgeable wait staff - highly recommend!!
Beautiful with great drinks
Everything was delicious including the Lamb Tartar, and the Duck. Nice ambiance location either inside or outside on the patio. Great date night spot.

This place is so dreamy, everything is delicious and staff were friendly. Our small plate food specials took an hour to get, hopefully an infrequent occurrence. And it was easy to forgive it since we were in a beautiful spot with wine and good service

Hands down one of the best restaurants in Harbor East. The Lobster Ravioli is amazing. We also tried the Tuscan Fried Chicken which was so tasty it should be offered as an entree. I finished my meal with the Squid Ink Campanelle and it was just as great as the rest of my meal. I shall return!!

Kitchen service  was horrible waited an hour and a half and no entrees. Red pepper bruschetta toast had a burnt flavor to point where you couldn't eat it. A tiny assistant Manger, with a Napoleon comple I might add, was extremely arrogant,  condescending and just plain rude. Certainly not worth the time or money. Our party was extremely disappointed.

It was a long time coming but we finally made it for lunch and the food, service and ambiance are amazing!  Fresh pasta, quality ingredients and a chef who knows what he is doing all add up to superior Italian cuisine.  The chicken I had in my marsala was fork tender and I have never had marsala with 4 different mushrooms in the sauce. Just plain excellence on a plate. Meatballs were awesome and the salad was excellent too.  A lot of attention to detail goes into the whole experience.  Check it out.
Receptionists receive you with cold face as if you are asking for a free meal!!! More over the food are way overpriced and the portions were minute..  food taste is very average...
The Food was AMAZING but the service was HORRIBLE!!!!
Thank you Stefan (waiter support and barback) for making the evening extra amazing at Tagliata! Keep up the great job!!!!
Creative Italian with excellent produce and ingredients.  Went for a celebratory dinner and truly enjoyed everything we ordered from appetizer to dessert. Definitely worth future visits.
Great ambiance with great food. Loved the food and drinks.

Best Restaurant in Baltimore Inner Harbor.  Appetizers are varied,  tasty and plentiful.  The scallop Crudito was magnificent.  Bolognese was superb. Service was wonderful with Piano music from the lounge that made the night romantic.  And of course Kieth set it all in motion with his timing. TERRIFIC NIGHT OUT.
A comfortable setting and exceptional food.
Great meal and wine selection.
My steak was delicious and the bartender was very friendly. I will definitely return.

I was afraid to go here because I thought it was too fancy and out of my price range but I went on a Wednesday afternoon and it was great. They have great happy hour deals and the outside area is beautiful and nice and relaxing.
Don't go here if you expect to get food within 2 and a half hours. Worst dining experience I've had in a long time
Great atmosphere very pricey!
Great food, great service
The BEST chicken marsala I have ever had.
Phenomenal food and service. One of the best Italian places in Baltimore.
Great food and beautiful setting!
2nd time here. The food, drinks and service is top notch. Would come back.

One of my favorite restaurants in the Inner Harbor. Service is always amazing and you will have trouble choosing what to eat (the menu is fantastic). Had the salmon this time and it was prepared perfectly. Not to be missed.
Bar service needs improvement!   Food was good.
The flavors were amazing!!

Disappointing best sums up my Tagliata experience. After having it recommended by numerous people, we visited on a Saturday night we had a reservation and were seated outside at a table next to the flowers. The quality of the food was okay at best. The main courses we ordered were both half pastas and were very good. The appetizers, however, were a terrible first impression. The meatball appetizer was just okay, but nothing special. The meat was a little salty and fatty and the sauce was just fine. The fried chicken appetizer was actually so bad we sent it back. It was coated in salt. I have had pretzels with less salt. It was a huge disappointment because the chicken looked like it could be good. Overall, the it was an okay experience, but for the price of the meal there are many better restaurants in Baltimore.
The food is exceptional, but your wait to eat it exceeds my patience. This is the kitchen and not the server, so don't blame the wait on bad service.

Fantastic atmosphere, great lightening, and energetic vibe. If you are dining with a large group of people I recommend calling in advance and reserving the back room for a secluded and personal dining experience. I had the duck with blueberries, porcini mushrooms and tadicchio  it was awesome.  Definitely top three duck I have eaten. I would also recommend for an appetizer trying the Tuscan Fried Chicken, with artichokes, lemon and garlic aioli. I wish I had some right now.

Atmosphere was nice- more old school, upscale inside, and more modern upscale in outside seating area- but the food left much to be desired. I had the meatballs as an app. They weren't bad, but at an ITALIAN restaurant, I was expecting them to be delicious. My main course was the house made pasta w mushrooms. It was not good. It tasted very boring and bland, like they had thrown just  some plain butter on top (for $36). Drinks were okay, and service was eh. Oh, and staff wore everything from casual jeans to incredibly inappropriate, ill-fitting attire. Conclusion: Overpriced menu for the quality of food. Will not be returning.
Food was amazing. Definitely not a romantic restaurant was really loud. Worth the trip and money. Plan at least a hundred per couple with out drinks.
Great food, menu, service, and atmosphere
Atmosphere and food were amazing.
Excellent food.  My only complaint would be the prices are high and the portions are tiny.
First visit for my birthday celebration.   The food was delicious and the staff were wonderful.   Hubby and I will this one of our date night restaurants.
Excellent food, great service, terrific sommelier

I visited Tagliata with my aunts and had a lovely time. The Happy Hour menu is extensive and fairly priced (small plates of a selection of their regular entrees are $6). We shared a few of the small plates and a charcuterie board and everything was great. We particularly enjoyed the Tuscan fried chicken and the Rigatoni alla vodka. One of my aunts also got the squid ink pasta and loved it (she said it was nearly as good as the version she had in Italy a few months ago). The atmosphere is lovely, with live piano music in the bar and soft lighting. We'll definitely be back and I would highly recommend for a date night!
Really tasty food.  I definitely plan on going back.
I had the Black ink pasta dish and it was delicious. Happy hour was a good time to try several dishes. The bartender Adrian was great. The whole staff and the atmosphere was wonderful!

Good food, gastro dishes, and excellent wine but overpriced and our server was not very attentive, and didn't seem all that concerned about my food allergies. He forgot a bunch of stuff too and we barely saw him after the initial order.
Cool spot. Great place for a Preakness after Party
Food was delicious. Ambiance was very nice. Not too pricey but not cheap. Treat yo self
Great food and I love the atmosphere, it’s just on the pricy side. Would recommend going for a nice dinner out. Their outdoor seating is nice as well if the weather is good.
Very good upscale italian

A great experience! My husband and I decided to go at the last minute without making reservations but they were nice enough to accomadate us on the spot. We started with some cocktails which were well mixed and their meatballs for appetizer, which was just very tasty. The entrees were really good as well, the service, the ambiance  all together just put you in a good relaxed mood! P.s. we already took our portions from the meatballs, so forgive the picture ..lol
Great variety
Very very tasty food, especially if your in the mood to try something different.
Exceptional service, great food, everything there is amazing!

Thoroughly disappointed with the biased and discriminatory attitude of the management/staff. While the dress code is displayed in the restaurant and on the website, I overlooked the no camouflage bullet -- no problem, except that there was a patron sitting in plain view of the two female hostess and any potential patron breaking several of the "mandatory dress codes" such as no hooded sweatshirts or sneakers. When brought to the hostesses attention all we got was a simple, "I see what you mean". When you allow certain patrons to blatantly violate the dress code and strictly enforce it with others, this becomes a discriminatory act. And to top it off, have said patron front and center to remind the ones you "CHOOSE" to turn away that the rules only apply to who you deem them suitable for is disrespectful and highly questionable.  It was a shameful and embarrassing experience to be turned away from an establishment that has proven they want to cater to a specific demographic who can come in sporting hooded sweatshirts and Vans. There's no other explanation other than the obvious. Stay away!

I have been to many nice restaurants.. However, I was extremely disappointed in the confusing, unfair business casual dress code at this restaurant. Business casual is business casual. The staff and managers do not strictly follow the so called "dress code". I was disappointed to see them let some people break the dress code while strictly upholding it with others. Its's blatantly disrespectful and a smack in the face to many you turned away. You let others stay while you selected what you considered business casual. 'As a professional  I know what business casual is and your policy of selecting who to allow and who not to allow is an utter FAIL!!. The individuals you allowed to sit at the bar and hang in the restaurant looked like they just woke up. Do better! Be Better! Stick with the policy all around or toss it. The worst experience ever!

The managers pick and choose  who they want to  uphold the dress code with. If you are going to turn away a potential patron then be consistent on your dress code requirements. We drove all the way from Perry hall for a birthday celebration only to be turned away because the birthday girl had on fashionable camouflage leggings. Ok I would be accepting of this turn away if I did not see other patrons with hoodies, jeans and sneakers. One girl had on a hoody, jeans, jean jacket and vans and they allowed her in. I will never advise any of my colleagues to visit your am establishment. You can not discriminate and choose who you are okay with breaking the rules with and who you want to uphold them with. Shame on you, your establishment and your managers.

0 Stars for me after having the worst experience I've ever had at a restaurant on April 12, I came here with a friend of mine who is a regular here she's a military veteran and had on her military jacket in which she always wear it here but on this particular night the 2 ladies at the front told her that she couldn't wear it when there was a sign displayed right in the front of us saying if you're military you could wear your military jacket the 2 ladies argued her for some time until my friend finally asked for a manager some young guy came saying he's the manager the 2 ladies approached him first he then turns around and says to my friend you must have on your full military uniform she was historical at this point I turned to her and said let's go in which we went to a better restaurant and was treated with dignity..I'll never visit Tagliata again. I'm from the Washington DC Nothern Virginia area where no one is treated like that and I informed my friends at our local newspapers about my experience at a Baltimore restaurant my experience was unprofessional and very disrespectful
The dry aged steaks are delicious!

Went there with pretty high expectations. We got a few cocktails, the burrata, the squid ink pasta, the NY dry-aged steak and the coconut panna cotta. Everything was pretty good except the steak. I was very disappointed and definitely did not worth the $65. Overcooked and chewy. Nick (the GM) tried to make up for it. It may have been a one-time thing but I wouldn’t risk it again. Nice place, friendly server. If I ever go back, I would only try their pasta.

Sat at the bar because it was too long a wait for a table so I can't comment on service but the food was fantastic.  The beef carpaccio was delicious. Fresh beef sliced oh so thin and beautifully seasoned. Topped with just enough little accoutrements to give it some texture.  The NY strip steak was one of the best I've ever had. Cooked perfectly it was tender and well seasoned. Absolutely incredible in every bite.  The tortellini was delicious. While it didn't go with the steak very well, that was my fault. Tender pasta with delicious prosciutto inside with just enough of a sweet sauce to balance things out.  The only thing I could even complain about in the slightest is that I wanted to try their morel mushroom bruschetta, but they were out.
Not a big selection of entrees however very tasty. Nice atmosphere. Just too many people (employees)  moving around doing this doing that, couldnt really enjoy our food. However, we will return.
Amazing risotto!!!
Awesome restaurant, great food and wine, excellent waiter "Jean!"
The piano player is amazing!  Best part of my Baltimore trip.
Pasta dishes were amazing. Didn't cook my steak right but the flavor and sauce was very good and unique.
Just loved it!!! Everything was great:)
Exceptional service. We were there for an anniversary and manager (Nick), server (Natasha) and team provided a wonderful experience.
Not what I expected but okay
Amazing outdoor patio!
Fantastic spot. The food was incredible, service was on point and the atmosphere was perfect.

Such a great experience. Able to sit on the patio on an unseasonably warm March day and the experience was wonderful. Started with the Tuscan Fried Chicken and Meatballs. Both incredible. Split the Squid Ink pasta, and tenderloin...delicious!! Service by Cassandra was impeccable. It's my third time, and I'll be back!

Tagliata is subtle perfection. We had some kind of salmon appetizer on a spoon. It was fantastic. This is not the place for people who want to stuff their face with whatever. If you appreciate delicious food then you will enjoy Tagliata.
The food and service are both outstanding. Highly recommend the eggplant parm

Came here for birthday drinks and quick eats at the outside bar. Staff was cool, chatty and nice.  Their house cocktails are great and the bartenders know how to make them really well. The atmosphere is pretty nice and this is a popular restaurant.

I loved my experience here. The menu had dishes I had never seen at any other restaurant around and it was so tough to choose what we wanted, but in the end we ordered the lobster ravioli and the squid ink campanelle. It was more than wonderful and I don't think you could ever say a dish had TOO much lobster in it but the lobster ravioli seemed like every bite was the most tender lobster ever. Highly recommended spot to go.

I went here for cocktails with my girlfriend on Valentine's Day waiting for our table at The Elk Room. The bartender had asked for our I.D.'s which is pretty normal for us but of course we are still plenty over 21. I happen to have a vertical ID from Virginia because I recently moved to Baltimore and my vertical ID doesn't expire until 2021 so I haven't switched it out yet. They refused my service after initially accepting my ID stating for Valentine's Day only they aren't accepting vertical id's because there are authorities checking to make sure businesses aren't serving underage people. It completely ruined our night and I blame Atlas Restaurant Group as owners because it happened at The Elk Room as well. And the reasoning behind not accepting my id at each place was different which is very concerning.
Good food, fair prices, good service.
First time here and everything was absolutely amazing. The food was delicious and service above and beyond. I thoroughly enjoyed my experience at Tagliata! Will definitely be back:)
Great food and service. Live music was too loud for a restaurant setting.
Love going to the bar with friends and listening to their live music. Can’t wait until the outdoor area is back in full swing come warmer weather.
Great meal out.
Wonderful food with great live music
Good ambience, great food and fine wine. Service can be a little quicker though.
Amazing!! Top notch food and service!
Great Italian place. Enjoined a very nice romantic dinner here. Loved everything we had.
Best Italian food in Baltimore!

The service and the atmosphere were incredible. Sadly I took my girlfriend here for her birthday when I happened to be sick so I paid for a nice dinner that I couldn’t really taste to due to my cold but I definitely want to return. I was able to get brief tastes of my food and it was pretty stellar on my brief impression.
Excellent food and service...a little loud and tables are close.
Lovely place, delicious food, great service. Will definitely be back!

Go for the drinks and charcuterie. Stay clear of the pasta.  Great atmosphere and top notch service put this chic restaurant as one of the best in Harbor East.  Used the valet, which is appropriately priced at $9. Seated very promptly with our 7:15 reservation. The place was packed, but was still able to talk to each other without yelling over the crowd. The interior is very comfortable and warm with interesting wood tones. The waiter promptly came to our table but gave us enough space to order without feeling pushy. His recommendations were scripted, he literally suggested all of the menu items and emphasized having charcuterie, app, pasta, steak. I don't know any couples that would order that much food. Cocktails were well made. Charcuterie is worth the trip alone. The meatballs were delicious. We had Bolognese (waiter said was the best he ever had) and Tortellini. Both pastas were bad. Bolognese noodles were dry and meat was gamy. The tortellini was too heavy on bacon.  Overall a great experience and would return to try the steak.
Sitting outside is a beautiful dining experience
For a place just outside Little Italy in Baltimore,  it was very good.  Great food.  Great service and definitely worth getting there.
We had the private room.  It was very nice.  The staff was excellent and the food was great!  Very aware & accommodating of dietary restrictions.  We made a great choice.  We would do it again.

First time here was for their New Year’s Eve party which was FANTSTIC! This group of restaurants teamed up their sister places The Elk Room and Italian Disco with Tagliata for a night of great food, excellent drinks and three types of entertainment. Piano Bar sing-a-long at Tagliata’s, 3-piece Jazz trio at The Elk Room and a DJ at Italian Disco. We party-hopped, ate, drank, danced and sang until the party was over at 3am!! That was a big deal for my friends and I being in our mid-40’s. We can only stay out that late when we’re having fun and we were, all night long! It was worth every penny of the ticket price and fees. We hope this party happens again next year but in the meantime, we plan on coming back throughout the year to all 3 places. Thank you for a great time!!
Amazing food and a great atmosphere.  The somm is the best in Baltimore, great wine picks.
Great food and atmosphere. Another fantastic offering from the Atlas Group.

Cozy and welcoming, for sure. Self parking is pretty bad, but we Uber'd so no issues there. Had the entire back room for our company dinner and the staff was so great. The bartenders downstairs were fantastic and we could have stayed all night!
Great service. Amazing cocktails and phenomenal beef tenderloin. Brussel sprouts and polenta both good side dishes.
Incredible dining experience. Amazing food and drinks, great ambiance and outstanding service
Best squid ink pasta with crab meat
This place is great.... But, you will have to pay.

Went to Tagliata last night for my wife's birthday.  We were engaged and married at Cingale (under Chef Julian), so we decided to try Tagliata, and we are GLAD WE DID.  The food was really great, and we are tough sells.  We started by splitting a carrot salad with fresh ricotta, which was fantastic.  The kitchen sent out a complimentary taste of their mushroom risotto next which was amazing...an umami masterpiece.  Then for our main course my wife had the squid ink pasta and shared one piece with me.  We were really blown away by the complexity and depth of flavor in this dish.  I had a full portion of the bolognese which was HUGE and very good!  I have left overs for lunch today.  We finished by splitting the dark chocolate cake which came with a complimentary trio of gelati.  Everything we had last night met or surpassed our expectations!  Service was great, prices reasonable for the amount of food we received, and flavors all on point.  We will definitely be back!
Food was incredible, great atmosphere, top-notch service. I'd definitely recommend!

I absolutely love this place! One of my Top 5 for suggested date nights. Great food, Sophisticated Environment!! Everytime I go the outside section is what attracts me, very beautiful but good idea to go when it’s warm out. They also have a speakeasy located in the back!!!

When life gives you Tagliata, you make reservations and have the most amazing dining experience. Thank you Alex and Eric for being such great hospitality brothers and friends! Adeleke, thank you for being a gracious host #AtlasFamily
Really nice, delicious food, too many white people
Great food and service. The bar is beautiful. Top notch spot. The only thing they can do is tone the music down a little. It's hard to talk at the bar.

Incredible. Everything was perfect. I strongly recommend trying the beef tartare, beet salad, bolognese, and/or the short ribs. The food was excellent but I think the service may have been even more impressive. Our server was amazing- …

I was treated here for my birthday (price wise, I could not afford this usually!) and I was so pleased! Very classy place with a great staff. The food was absolutely delicious. I had the lobster ravioli and it melted in my mouth. The bruschetta was another notable dish :) I look forward to being able to enjoy Tagliata again, soon!

The ambiance at Tagliata is wonderful. Just the right amount of music, lighting, and wine selection to make for a wonderful experience. We showed up with very short notice and the staff was wonderful and accommodated us within minutes. I ordered the Saltimbocca and my friend ordered the Chicken Marsala , both were exquisite and the portions were fantastic and not over- filling. The service was great and without a doubt I recommend this spot for just about any thing from dinner date, drinks & dinner with friends, business dinner, birthday dinner, etc. I cannot wait to return!
Great service and great food. Part of a trilogy of places.
(Translated by Google) Exquisite food, good place for dinner  (Original) Exquisita comida buen lugar para cenar
Great good, small plates.

Excellent food & service; you leave feeling you had a great dining experiance, finished by a visit to "THE ELK ROOM" across the patio and that's an un-paralelled finish to a wonderful night. Accented by Valet parking makes Tagliata an easily repeatable/desirable venue.

The Food was good, the service was good the Primitivo was excellent but a couple of things totally spoiled it for me. I was at a table in the corner up against the wallpaper. In the corner of my eye I kept seeing something on the wall moving when I looked up to see what was distracting me I saw cobwebs of dust stuck to the wallpaper and if you follow that up to the ceiling it's obvious that the heat registers have not been cleaned in years. Looking around a bit more the mirrors above my head and along the side wall have not been cleaned for a long time either. And the final thing I asked the waiter what coffee they used and he had to think hard but finally said Illy which I love so I ordered a latte, I'd bet money it was not.
Great atmosphere and incredible food.  The charcuterie boards are a staple and a must have!
Cool decor and vibe but the food was not that good.  We had the steak, which I would never order again, but the marinara sauce on the meatball appetizer was amazing.

FANTASTIC birthday dinner here! Had a party of 7 and everyone was treated well. The apps were delicious, the cocktails were well mixed, and the food came out perfect. From the valet to the waitstaff service was superior. Will absolutely go back.

Meh. We had been wanting to try Tagliata for a while now, and we have a completely mixed review about the experience. First, I had been looking for weeks for reservations on OpenTable and it literally shows every Friday and Saturday night booked for the foreseeable future. We were catching a movie in Harbor East and upon seeing that Tagliata again had no reservations, we walked in at 645 on Friday night hoping to snag a seat at the bar, only to find a mostly empty restaurant and the hostess was able to seat us at a table. A nice surprise, but either something is not right with their settings in OT or they are intentionally trying to keep up an air that they are always booked, which is fine, but not a great strategy for getting in local folks who have to plan ahead.  That said, the place is exceptionally beautiful and felt like we were not in Baltimore. Very sleek, upscale vibes, and a combination of comfortable chair and booth seating. The service was spotty. The hostess didn't offer to take my coat, and our server forgot my date's drink order. Support staff (bread / cheese, bussers, runners) were all spot on.  The menu was interesting without trying too hard and I really appreciated that there were some great, high end wines offered by the glass, price not withstanding (although most of the list was very reasonable). I had a bruschetta which was delicious and my date the tortellini soup (also great), but his main dish is where Tagliata lost us. We paid $56 for a lobster ravioli that was practically raw. I love an al dente pasta, but for $60 it better be damn perfect and it wasn't even close. Flavor was good but was ruined by the doughy, raw texture. My beef tortellini was really delicious and the half portion was generous.  It was overall a decent experience, but if you are going to charge $50+ per plate, everything better be perfect, and Tagliata fell short.
Love this Atlas group offering.  Food and atmosphere are vibrant and always on point
Food was good service a little slow the night I went
A little pricey but the food was fabulous and the wait staff was great

This place has a lot of potential. The music is too loud at the bar, I love the era but they are cramming it down the patrons throats. The Bolognese would be perfect if they would reduce the sodium. The service is excellent.
The service was as outstanding as the food. Our daughter was on liberty and it was such a fantastic experience for her... actually, the whole family. We will definitely visit again!

Terrific place! Lots of thing are made in house, which I appreciate  a lot, cured meats, mozzarella,  pasta. Kitchen staff works hard to make dinner special. Julian is a favorite chef - talented and hardworking.
Great pasta. Great atmosphere. A must place to eat at Baltimore.

Excellent ambience, especially outside with the heaters. The service was decent and I loved having a cheeseman come by and slice me a piece! I ordered the carbonara and for the price ($18 for half-plate), it was unimpressive. Not quite enough sauce and it was topped with thick bacon pieces that were too salty and overpowering. The broccoli was similar - overly salted. I'd probably go back for drinks outside but not to eat.
Very attentive staff - excellent. Food was tasty. Portioned well. Nice drink menu.

Great service! Carrot salad, chicken masala, cheese board were all amazing! Squash bruschetta was good but not as great. Chocolate fudge cake was my favorite! The lemoncello shots at the end were a bit much for my taste but I am sure people love them! Overall one of the best restaurants in the city!

Excellent service start to finish. The food was delectable. I chose the farfalle with Sausage, great spicy slow burn! Our server was top notch in my book. Took care of our every need. I definitely recommend you try Tagliota if you haven't yet!
Very good food, kind of loud,  friendly and helpful staff
Very good service and good food!
Now the best Italian restaurant of the city. Food is delicious and no too expensive like others.
Spectacular food and service. Just a wee bit too loud: the ambient music
Beautiful outside dining area and bar area!

Amazing menu with exceptional service. Do yourself a favor and download the 33 page wine list for review prior to your arrival. My wife and I went for our anniversary and were greeted with a personalized card as we were seated. Our server Jessica was outstanding, explaining dishes, suggesting pairings and overall ensuring we thouroghly enjoyed our evening.
Outstanding food sn service
Great food and service. Simple, delicious and great charcuterie selections.
Beyond amazing.  The decor is incredible.  Service is outstanding.  And every dish we had was absolutely mind-blowing.  This is true dining at it's finest.  We will be back!
Delicious food, but entrees come in smaller portions. Beautiful space. Bread and cheese crumbles from a fanny pack. Good wine list.

Food was fantastic. So many options. Pricey for sure. Was lucky to be at a work function. Be forewarned.. the squid ink pasta is amazing, but you will poop black for two weeks... I still highly recommend it. 🙃
lovely decor and space empty  for weekday lunch oberpco ed salads shrimp over cooked. ..desert on thw  house great svc will try again
Great food, service and al fresco dining. We celebrated our parents 47th Wedding Anniversary here, Tagliata went ABOVE and beyond to make our celebration special. All around wonderful experience.
Amazing food selection and the service is top notch.

This is an amazing gem.  First, the happy hour is a great deal. Drinks and food are affordable.  They have giant menu and all fresh made pasta.  We got two pasta dishes the lobster fra diavolo and this ink squid pasta with crab.  They were both amazing! Then we had a fish dish and it was also so amazing! This was a stellar meal with great service

Very classy experience all around. Every staff member is attentive but doesn’t give the hovering sensation. The food is second to none and the drinks are truly craft cocktails. The outside seating is great in nice weather and the inside music is usually accompanied with a piano/singer. Well worth the premium price.
Great Meal! The softshell crabs were outstanding!
Excellent food but we spent a long time waiting for it and we got no bread while we were waiting.

Tagliata is where we decided to celebrate our 4th anniversary and I'm so glad we did.  Fresh bread and parma-regg cheese is served via a gentleman walking around with a basket.  Hubs got the pasta bolignese  and he was very happy with his dinner. I got the half order of the lobster ravioli and it was the best thing that I have had to eat in a very long time. That being said, $26 for six ravioli is a little too steep of a price for me.  I did notice servers walking by as they were serving food, and the food servings seems to be a little small to me. It is a great place to go for dinner, but don't be surprise if you leave hungry.  Flavors of the food were absolutely delicious, but the price is just way too expensive for what you get.
1st time here! Excellent! Will be back!
We had an amazing dinner at Tagliata. Everything was great, but the squid ink pasta was the best thing we ate. Can't wait to come back

Great wine selection, I had the bolognese which was really good. The carbonara was underwhelming. All the other food and service was great. They have a nice happy hour as well but seating for it is limited. Definitely on my list of top HH spots

Expensive but worth the money. One of the better meals that I have had in Baltimore. Service was on point. My aged steak was excellent, and the squid ink pasta was amazing.  The meat cheese board was very good - 3 out of 4 items were great, but the local salami was just so-so. An excellent spot for a high end date.
This is a go to for me. Happy hour is fantastic, especially if there is seating outside available. The egg plant parm and squid ink pasta are second to none.

Food was just OK. The atmosphere is lively, but it is loud and hard to talk. Drinks are really expensive!! ( I had a Kentucky Mule and my buddy got a Blantons Bourbon on the rocks--$ 18 $ 19 !! 2 glasses of wine were $16 - $18 !! )Overall average and way overpriced. For the money, go to LaScala or Aldo's. Better food with smaller bill
